article.headline: Auburn 77, Alabama St. 72
article.story: AUBURN, Ala. -- Tay Waller scored 21 points as Auburn beat Alabama State 77-72 on Monday night. The win was the fourth straight victory for the Tigers (7-4). Waller shot 7-for-14 from the field, including 6-for-12 from 3-point range. Rasheem Barrett chipped in with 12 points. Brandon Brooks led the Hornets (2-7) with 24 points and seven assists. Rashad Provitt added 14 points and 14 rebounds. The Hornets held a 29-24 lead at halftime, but Auburn opened the second half with an 11-6 run -- which included eight points from Waller -- to tie the game. Alabama State battled back to regain the lead, and led 48-38 with 10:52 remaining. Auburn answered with a 17-0 run with 2:25 remaining to gain a 59-68 lead, and never trailed again. Auburn scored 31 points off of Alabama State's 24 turnovers.
